)attr default(%+$)
  $ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>$ZCMD
+
                          %Finding your SSH Public Key
+
%1.+From within zigi on the Local Repositories Panel
%2.+Enter the command%SSH+
%3.+Select your SSH Public Key using your TN3270 emulator and copy it
+   to your workstations clipboard.
%4.+It is now ready to be pasted into the Git server of your choice.
+
%Alternate approach
+
%1.+Download to your workstation from your home directory the%.ssh/id_rsa.pub
+   file. It should NOT be downloaded in binary as it is a text file.
%2.+Open the file in Notepad or similar text editor
%3.+Use Control-A (in Windows) to select all to copy the key to the workstations
+   clipboard.
%4.+It is now ready to be pasted into the Git server of your choice.
+
+
+        +Press the%Enter+key to continue your zigi tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
 &zgsr = CSR
)PROC
 &zcont = zigih710
)END
